# Cursor Rules for Manna LLM Aster Crypto Trader

## Code Style Guidelines

### NO EMOJIS IN CODE
- **NEVER use emojis in code files** (TypeScript, JavaScript, etc.)
- Use text prefixes instead: `[OK]`, `[ERROR]`, `[WARN]`, `[INFO]`, `[START]`, `[SUCCESS]`, etc.
- Emojis are acceptable ONLY in documentation files (README.md, docs/*.md)
- This ensures code is clean, professional, and compatible with all terminals/editors

### Logging Format
- Use consistent prefixes: `[OK]`, `[ERROR]`, `[WARN]`, `[INFO]`, `[DEBUG]`, `[START]`, `[SUCCESS]`
- Example: `logger.info('[OK] Model loaded successfully', { ... })`
- Example: `console.log('[ERROR] Failed to connect')`

### Code Quality
- Always use TypeScript strict mode
- Prefer async/await over promises
- Use meaningful variable names
- Add JSDoc comments for public methods
- Keep functions focused and single-purpose

